#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Theorem]
#title[Normal form of vector fields]

Let $M$ be a #link("009D")[smooth n-dimensional manifold] equipped with a #link("009S")[smooth vector field] $X: M -> T M$. For a every point $p in M$ where the $X$ does not vanish, there is a local chart $kappa: Uu ->  Vv$ of $M$ around $p$, such that the $X$ is given by a constant function in this chart.

Concretely such that for all $x in Uu$ $D_(x)kappa (X (x)) =  e_(1)$, the first basis vecotor of the standard basis.
